# ============================================================
# Rutba POS — Environment Configuration
# ============================================================
#
#  TWO LOADING MODES
#  ─────────────────
#  The env system (scripts/load-env.js, scripts/generate-docker-env.js)
#  operates in one of two modes, chosen automatically:
#
#  ┌─────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
#  │ File mode   │ .env file EXISTS at repo root               │
#  │ (default)   │ 1. .env  →  selects ENVIRONMENT             │
#  │             │ 2. .env.<ENVIRONMENT>  →  full config        │
#  │             │ File values override process.env             │
#  ├─────────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
#  │ Env-var mode│ NO .env file (Docker / CI)                  │
#  │             │ ENVIRONMENT from process.env (default: dev)  │
#  │             │ All config from process.env                  │
#  │             │ Only NEXT_PUBLIC_* and PREFIX__* collected    │
#  └─────────────┴─────────────────────────────────────────────┘
#
#  VARIABLE SPLITTING
#  ──────────────────
#  scripts/load-env.js reads variables and splits them into two types:
#
#    GLOBAL — no __ delimiter → injected into EVERY app
#      NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:4010/api/
#
#    APP-SPECIFIC — WORKSPACE_NAME__VARNAME → prefix + __
#      stripped, injected only into that app
#      POS_AUTH__PORT=4003        →  PORT=4003      (pos-auth only)
#      RUTBA_WEB__NEXTAUTH_SECRET=abc  →  NEXTAUTH_SECRET=abc  (rutba-web only)
#
#  Prefix = workspace directory name, uppercased, hyphens → _
#    pos-strapi      → POS_STRAPI__
#    pos-auth        → POS_AUTH__
#    rutba-web       → RUTBA_WEB__
#    rutba-web-user  → RUTBA_WEB_USER__
#    rutba-rider     → RUTBA_RIDER__
#    rutba-social    → RUTBA_SOCIAL__
#
#  VALIDATION
#  ──────────
#  Required variables are defined in scripts/env-config.js.
#  The loader will:
#    - ERROR and abort on missing critical variables (severity: 'error')
#    - WARN but continue on missing optional variables (severity: 'warn')
#
#  The target app is auto-detected from --workspace= or --prefix
#  in the command — no redundant app argument needed:
#    "dev:auth": "node scripts/load-env.js -- npm run dev --workspace=pos-auth"
#
#  CORS: Strapi receives a CORS_ORIGINS env var auto-computed
#        from every URL value in the env file. No manual list.
#
#  PORT RESOLUTION
#  ───────────────
#  PORT is only set when explicitly configured:
#    1. process.env.PORT (platform/host override — ALWAYS wins)
#    2. PREFIX__PORT in env file (e.g. POS_AUTH__PORT=4003)
#
#  No PORT is auto-derived from URLs. If neither is set, the app
#  uses its own default.
#
#  On managed platforms (Hostinger, Railway, Azure App Service) the
#  platform sets PORT automatically. The loader respects it.
# ============================================================

ENVIRONMENT=development
